N PLANNING GUIDELINE #4-1 ... 28 \nATTACHMENT J NYISO TRANSMISSION PLANNING GUIDELINE #5-0 ... 32 \nATTACHMENT K COST ALLOCATION PROCEDURES PURSUANT CLASS YEAR 2001 SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT ... 34 \nATTACHMENT L NORMAL ISO OPERATING PROCEDURES ... 41 \n\nTransmission Expansion and Interconnection Manual | v\n\nTable of Figures\n\nFigure 1: Deposits Associated with the NYISO TIP ... 5 \nFigure 2: Sections of the NYISO OATT Related to the Interconnection Process ... 28 \nFigure 3: Deposits Associated with the NYISO LFIP ... 31 \nFigure 4: Exporting and Importing Regions for Highways ... 74 \nFigure 5: Exporting and Importing Regions for Other Interfaces ... 76 \nFigure 6: Review of Cases to Evaluate Transfer ... 79 \nFigure 7: Exhibit I - Voltage-Limited Power Transfer ... 21 \n\nTransmission Expansion and Interconnection Manual | vi\n\nRevision History\n\nVersion Date Revisions\n\n1.0 09/01/1999 Initial Release \n2.0 11/01/2012 Significant update and rewrite \n2.1 10/30/2015 Additional updates are being made to this manual, including \nupdates to reflect revisions to Attachments S, X and Z to the NYISO \nOATT effective February 18, 2013 (FERC Docket Nos. ER13-588- \n001 & ER13-588-002) and revisions to Attachments X and Z \neffective February 14, 2014 (FERC Docket No. ER14-627-000) \nGlobal \n Reformatted per new template to standardize presentation \n Standardized labeling and numbering of graphical and tabular \nmaterial \nSection 2.4.2 \n Update the MW threshold for Requiring a Transmission System \nImpact Study (SIS) \nSection 2.4.3 \n Elimination of redundant language \nAttachment C \n Removed and updated all cross-references. Incorporated into \nthe Transmission Congestion Contracts Manual \nAttachment D \n Corrected footnote cross-references \n3.0 06/30/2017 Updates to conform with several tariff changes made between \nJanuary 2013 through August 2016, including: \n Class Year process changes limits and rules re. Commercial \nOperation Dates (tariff changes